dc:date  a      owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_578  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Postsynaptic knock-down (KD) of Complexin-1 and -2 (shRNA stereotactic in vivo injection into CA1 region of the hippocampus) blocks LTP (Fig. 1 F), indicating that Complexin plays a role in postsynaptic membrane fusion events underlying the exocytosis of AMPA receptors during LTP.\n\nNMDA-Receptor mediated LTD is unaffected by postsynaptic Complexin KD (Fig. 1 H).\n\nBlock of LTP can be rescued by expression of a shRNA-resitant full-length Complexin-1 variant (Fig. 1 G).\n\nBasal synaptic transmission is not affected by postsynaptic Complexin KD in slices (Fig.2) and cultures (Fig 4B), indicating that Complexin only regulates AMPA-Receptor exocytosis.. Experimental description: Stereotaxic injections of lentiviruses were made into the CA1 region of P18-22 C57BL/6 mice ..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_578" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

